context: The state is among the best in pre-kindergarten education, and the <a0_0>National Institute for Early Education Research<a0_0/> rated it first in the United States with regard to standards, quality, and access to pre-kindergarten education in <a1_0>2004<a1_0/>, calling it a model for early childhood schooling. High school dropout rate decreased from <a2_0>3.1<a2_0/> to <a3_0>2.5 percent<a3_0/> between 2007 and 2008 with Oklahoma ranked among 18 other states with 3 percent or less dropout rate. In 2004, the state ranked 36th in the nation for the relative number of adults with high school diplomas, though at <a4_0>85.2 percent<a4_0/>, it had the highest rate among southern states.
